# ── Personal logins (NOT app env vars — included so this file covers EVERY vault item)
OBSIDIAN_USERNAME=op://web-variables/Obsidian/username
OBSIDIAN_PASSWORD=op://web-variables/Obsidian/password
MACBOOKPRO_USERNAME=op://web-variables/MacbookPro/username
MACBOOKPRO_PASSWORD=op://web-variables/MacbookPro/password
# `Elgato` item exists but stores no value fields — nothing to resolve.


# ── Ops alerting (off-Mac paging) — NOT op-resolvable, set directly (like the bootstrap token)
# notify-ops.sh pages here on a RED from a routine (infra-health, ...). Deliberately Mac-local,
# NOT an op:// secret: a liveness probe's alert path must not depend on 1Password being up. The
# ntfy topic is obscurity, not a credential. Set on the Mac in ~/.config/schnapp-os/ops.env (chmod 600):
#   NTFY_URL=https://ntfy.sh/<random-topic>
NTFY_URL=
# Optional explicit GitHub token for the alert path, so `gh` does not rely on the macOS keyring being
# readable by launchd (verified readable today via the GUI LaunchAgent, but this makes it deterministic).
# A token with `repo` (or issues:write) scope. Mac-local in ops.env; refresh with: GH_TOKEN=$(gh auth token).
GH_TOKEN=


# ── SSH key — NOT a .env value (multi-line PEM). The `GitHub SSH Key` item holds the
# keypair; retrieve it with `op read` straight into ~/.ssh, never into this file.
